  "event_preview": "Watkins Glen International is a 2.454 mile (3.949 km) 11-turn permanent road course in Schuyler County, New York. The Mission 200 at The Glen is the thirteenth race of the 2026 NASCAR O'Reilly Auto Parts Series season and the second road course event of the year, run over 82 laps (201.288 miles) with stage breaks at laps 20 and 40. With 38 entries for 38 available positions, the full field is set to start. NASCAR Cup Series full-timers Connor Zilisch, Shane van Gisbergen and Ross Chastain all pull triple duty this weekend, racing in the Truck, O'Reilly and Cup events across three consecutive days.\n\nJustin Allgaier leads the O'Reilly championship standings heading in, having won four races in the first twelve events. Zilisch has won the O'Reilly Series race here in each of his two previous starts at Watkins Glen — his 2024 debut and the 2025 running — making him the prohibitive road course favourite on the strength of results that include a dominant 2025 win leading the most laps. Terry Labonte and Marcos Ambrose are the only other drivers in series history to win three consecutive O'Reilly races at Watkins Glen — a mark Zilisch would equal with a third straight victory.\n\nThe all-time O'Reilly Series qualifying record at Watkins Glen belongs to Zilisch, who turned a 71.028-second lap at 124.176 mph in 2024 qualifying — his first ever O'Reilly Series laps at the circuit. The race lap record is held by Zilisch as well, a 72.843-second best set during his 2025 victory.",
